Although preparations for the Naishidokoro Mikagura were made in December of Bunmei 5, a lack of financial support from the shogunate delayed the ceremony.{{Sfn|Makoto Nakamoto|2021|p=120-121}} However, in Bunmei 6 (1474), under strong insistence from {{ill|Emperor Go-Tsuchimikado|ja|後土御門天皇}}, the performance was held, with the emperor personally attending.{{Sfn|Makoto Nakamoto|2021|p=125-129}} The court summoned underground poets {{ill|Tachūei|ja|多忠英}} and {{ill|Takuji|ja|多久時}}, overcoming significant challenges.{{Sfn|Makoto Nakamoto|2021|p=130}} It is recorded that the kagura performance was attended by nobles as well as lower-ranking officials and a large audience of men and women.{{Sfn|Makoto Nakamoto|2021|p=129}}== See Also ==
